quran[25]{c,v,t,f}:
  69,52,"So glorify the Name of your Lord, the Most Great.{1}",footnotes:1:(V.52) See footnotes of (V.13:28).
  74,31,"And We have set none but angels as guardians of the Fire. And We have fixed their number (19) only as a trial for the disbelievers, in order that the people of the Scripture (Jews and Christians) may arrive at a certainty [that this Qur’ân is the truth as it agrees with their Books regarding the number (19) which is written in the Taurât (Torah) and the Injeel (Gospel)] and that the believers may increase in Faith (as this Qur’ân is the truth), and that no doubt may be left for the people of the Scripture and the believers, and that those in whose hearts is a disease (of hypocrisy) and the disbelievers may say: "
  74,32,"Nay! And by the moon"
  74,33,"And by the night when it withdraws."
  75,28,"And he (the dying person) will conclude that it was (the time) of parting (death);"
  75,29,"And one leg will be joined with another leg (shrouded).{1}",footnotes:1:(V.29) Or it may mean: hardship and distress will be joined with another hardship and distress (i.e. distress of death, and of the thought as to what is going to happen to him in the Hereafter). (Tafsîr At-Tabarî ).
  75,30,"The drive will be, on that Day, to your Lord (Allâh)!"
  76,22,"(And it will be said to them): "
  76,23,"Verily, it is We Who have sent down the Qur’ân to you (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم) by stages."
  76,24,"Therefore be patient (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم) with constancy to the Command of your Lord (Allâh, by doing your duty to Him and by conveying His Message to mankind), and obey neither a sinner nor a disbeliever among them."
  77,19,"Woe that Day to the deniers (of the Day of Resurrection)!"
  77,20,"Did We not create you from a despised water (semen)?"
  77,21,"Then We placed it in a place of safety (womb),"
  78,16,"And gardens of thick growth."
  78,17,"Verily, the Day of Decision is a fixed time,"
  78,18,"The Day when the Trumpet will be blown, and you shall come forth in crowds (groups after groups). [Tafsir At-Tabari]"
  79,10,"They say: "
  79,11,""
  79,12,"They say: "
  80,7,"What does it matter to you if he will not become pure (from disbelief: you are only a Messenger, your duty is to convey the Message of Allâh)."
  80,8,"But as to him who came to you running,"
  80,9,"And is afraid (of Allâh and His punishment)."
  81,4,"And when the pregnant she-camels are neglected;"
  81,5,"And when the wild beasts are gathered together."
  81,6,"And when the seas become as blazing Fire or overflow."